{"title": "Never Gets Fat", "content": "Lelouch: \"How is it you manage not to get fat, if all you ever eat is pizza? I never see you do anything more strenuous than walk across campus, and you only do that to annoy me between classes.\"\n\nWhenever a character eats too much food, no matter how much or how unhealthy, this person just won't gain a huge gut or end up in a mobile chair. Maybe they will but only in a few seconds of screen time as a gag or perhaps a Very Special Episode. Then they will go back to fighting bad guys or performing neat moves like back flips.\n\nA common justification would be that such characters are always active (like running every day, fighting bad guys that always cause trouble, or carrying heavy objects everywhere they go), they use magic, they were born with have a high level of metabolism, or the food they eat is healthy. This trope can be Zig Zagged if the character is fat in short time, but gets skinny and/or fit again afterwards.\n\nThis often happens to a Big Eater. Compare Hyperactive Metabolism, where a video game character regains HP/stamina through eating, usually with no weight related consequences.", "url": "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/NeverGetsFat", "media_links": ["/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Franchise/DragonBall", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/FairyTail", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Anime/KOn", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Franchise/LyricalNanoha", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Anime/MagicalGirlLyricalNanohaStrikers", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/MissKobayashisDragonMaid", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/MyHeroAcademia", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/Naruto", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/OnePiece", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Anime/PantyAndStockingWithGarterbelt", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Anime/Slayers", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/Toriko", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/ComicBook/ArchieComics", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/ComicBook/EarthX", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Franchise/DCAU", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Franchise/OnePiece", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/LabyrinthsOfEcho", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series